---
import ArticleLayout from "../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";

const pageTitle =
  "A 5-Minute Checklist Before Your Cleaning Visit | Expert Tips | Empire Cleaning Group";
const heading = "A 5-Minute Checklist Before Your Cleaning Visit";
const description =
  "Simple preparation steps to help your appointment run smoothly and efficiently.";
---

<ArticleLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  heading={heading}
  backHref="/en/conseils"
  backLabel="← Back to expert tips"
>
  <div class="article-meta" style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: #666; font-style: italic;">
    <span>Category: Guide</span> | <span>Updated: December 12, 2024</span>
  </div>

  <p class="lead" style="font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 500;">
    You booked an appointment—great! Here is how you can help us deliver the best possible service in a few simple steps.
  </p>

  <div
    style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 4px;"
  >
    <p style="margin: 0;">
      <strong>Reminder:</strong> these steps free our technicians to focus on extraction and cleaning quality—not on moving fragile items.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Clear walkways</h2>
  <p>
    Remove small objects, toys, fragile lamps, and floor plants from the areas to be cleaned. We need room to maneuver our hoses.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Furniture: we handle the heavy lifting (within reason)</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>What we move:</strong> sofas, coffee tables, chairs. We place small foam blocks under the feet after cleaning.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>What you should leave in place:</strong> filled bookcases, pianos, TV units with complex electronics, waterbeds. For these items, we clean carefully around them.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Vacuuming?</h2>
  <p>
    Ideally, a quick vacuum pass helps remove surface lint and debris, but our equipment will handle deep extraction either way.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Parking</h2>
  <p>
    Our truck-mount unit needs to park as close as possible to your door to maintain hot water temperature. If you can free up the driveway entrance, that’s ideal!
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
